column1: #Text=The Indiana Pacers defeated the Charlotte Hornets , 110 - 94 , at Bankers Life Fieldhouse on Wednesday .
#Text=Indiana was expected to win this game easily and they left no doubt with this overtime win .

column6: game did not go into overtime

column1: #Text=In fact , the Pacers led for the entirety of the second half , as they outscored the Hornets , 34 - 21 , in the fourth quarter .

column6: Pacers did not lead the whole 2nd half[1]

column1: #Text=Rebounding was a huge factor in the win , with the Pacers winning that battle , 42 - 34 .
#Text=The Hornets ( 14 - 11 ) have now won five of their last seven games , as they continue to play well .
#Text=Kemba Walker did all he could for Charlotte , as he led the team with 12 points , two rebounds and five assists .

column1: #Text=Nicolas Batum was second on the team , as he accrued 13 points , 10 rebounds and three assists .
#Text=Cody Zeller was the only other starter in double figures , as he accrued 11 points , seven rebounds and two blocks .

column1: #Text=On deck for Charlotte is a road matchup with the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday .
#Text=The Pacers ( 13 - 12 ) have now won five of their last six games , as they continue to look like a great team .
#Text=Paul George was the player of the game , as he accumulated 22 points , five rebounds and three assists .
